periments, Romanian seems to entail more subjectivity markers compared to English, and this factor motivates us to further pursue the use of languagespecific clues of subjectivity.
    Our experiments have generated corpora of about 20,000 sentences annotated for subjectivity in Romanian and Spanish, which are available for download at http://lit.csci.unt.edu/index.php/Downloads, along with the manually annotated data sets.
  
  
    The authors are grateful to Daniel Marcu and LanguageWeaver for kindly providing access to their Romanian-English and English-Romanian machine translation engines.
    This work was partially supported by a National Science Foundation grant IIS#0840608.
  

